{"key":"processedPost-12771281","value":{"id":12771281,"first":12769904,"last":12771281,"when":1277008423,"utime":"06/20/10 07:33 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>Nanoid said:</b><br />Lets say I mist a cake and it is shining/glistening with moisture. And lets say 3 hours later the cake isn't shiny anymore, but seemingly 'dry' (at least on the surface).&nbsp; Do I re-mist immediately after the cake isn't shiny anymore, or should I wait a hour or two before re-misting?<br /><br />Thanks!<br /></blockquote><br /><br />An hour or two after it no longer glistens.&nbsp; You want to let a bit of moisture evaporate from the cake, and then mist to replenish it.&nbsp; This ebb and flow of moisture content is a major pinning trigger.<br />RR","title":"Re: When to re-mist after evaporation of water from cake?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}